President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of West Virginia due to severe storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from June 29 to June 30, 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Jason Burroughs has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on additional damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.